	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes, you can use 29C256, but it (and other Atmel chips) require different programming algorithms than most other Flash, so check your programmer for support.
<br />
<br />Why do you want to make a NROM cart with 4M ROM? You do realize that 93% and 98% of the ROMs respectively will be wasted?
<br />
<br />If you're going to make your own board, design your own mapper to make use of the ROM or at least put switches to allow multiple games to be stored.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


